<pre class="highlight"><code><span class='kr'>class</span> <span class='nx'>Group</span> <span class='kr'>extends</span> <a href='/docs/reference/pkg/nodejs/pulumi/pulumi/#CustomResource'>CustomResource</a></code></pre>

Resource for managing QuickSight Group

#### Example Usage

```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as aws from "@pulumi/aws";

const example = new aws.quicksight.Group("example", {
    groupName: "tf-example",
});
```

#### Import

QuickSight Group can be imported using the aws account id, namespace and group name separated by `/`.

```sh
 $ pulumi import aws:quicksight/group:Group example 123456789123/default/tf-example
```

Resource for managing QuickSight User

#### Example Usage

```typescript
import * as pulumi from "@pulumi/pulumi";
import * as aws from "@pulumi/aws";

const example = new aws.quicksight.User("example", {
    email: "author@example.com",
    identityType: "IAM",
    userName: "an-author",
    userRole: "AUTHOR",
});
```

#### Import

Importing is currently not supported on this resource.
